QMSrs Representative Agreement
Date: DD/MM.YYYY
Parties:
This Joint Venture Agreement is made between QMS Resourcing Services Ltd (registered number:
03836478) of 141 Cutenhoe Road, Luton, Bedfordshire, United Kingdom (“QMSrs”)
and
Representative Name ,Address.
Term
This Agreement shall commence on the date it is signed by both Parties (the "Commencement Date") and
shall continue unless terminated in accordance with the terms herein.
Background
QMSrs has been seeking a reliable and professional channel for marketing its Training Courses, with local
market knowledge and contacts of the Jordan region, to promote and sell its Training Course.
Purpose
QMSrs and “Representative Name” wish to enter into an Agreement to Training Course market within
Jordan. “Representative Name” will operate as an independent representative and shall be rewarded with
commission payments as detailed below.
QMSrs will provide all the technical knowledge, the training courses and trainers as required.
“Representative Name” will provide all the marketing and sales activity.
Scope of Agreement
“Representative Name” will act as a Representative of QMSrs within Jordan on a non-exclusive basis and
will provide the following services:
1. Assist QMSrs to market its Training Courses in the Jordan territory
2. I
ntroduce QMSrs to new customers (those unknown to QMSrs at the time of introduction)
3. P
rovide all the marketing & sales, administration and also generate appropriate marketing collateral
(presentation, brochures etc.). QMSrs will provide support for this activity
Contribution from Each Party:
1. QMSrs will provide the following services and products:
 Make available all of QMSrs Training Courses and the e-Learning solutions for delivering some
of these course for “Representative Name” to promote and sell to any customer within Jordan.
 Provide full training for “Representative Name” to ensure a good level of understanding of the
products
 Support “Representative Name” with pre-sales and after-sales service
 Provide appropriate resources where necessary to facilitate the Sales process

 QMSrs will honour confidentiality with “Representative Name”
2. “Representative Name” will provide the following services:
 Market and sell all QMSrs Training Courses without exception
 Ensure that QMSrs activity is the main focus for “Representative Name”
 Other “Representative Name” activities must not conflict with QMSrs
 “Representative Name” will generate an agreed marketing strategy and detailed sales forecast
 “Representative Name” will be responsible for on-going marketing to achieve agreed objectives
 “Representative Name” will provide full visibility of the status of all activities, financial,
technical and operational
Commission Payment
As a reward for the tasks performed and sales closed by “Representative Name” ; QMSrs will pay a
commission as follows:
 For all Training Courses sold and successfully delivered; 50% of the Net Profit.
 Finders Fee: 2% of the Sales Price for any customers introduced to QMSrs either for Training or
any other products.
Notes:
1. The commission fee will only be paid to “Representative Name” after the customer has paid
QMSrs.
2. The Net Profit means the profit made by QMSrs after all the costs (i.e. conference rooms, food,
refreshments, trainers fees etc.) have been accounted for. e.g.
Sales Price JD100
Cost of sales JD20 (directly sales associated with sale – e.g. trainer fees)
Gross Profit JD80
Other Expenses JD40
Net Profit JD40 (“Representative Name” will get JD20)
3. Finders Fee means where “Representative Name” has only introduced the customer to QMSrs and
has taken no further active part in ‘winning’ that customer.
4. Commission Fee means where “Representative Name” has actively been involved in the
marketing, selling and administration of Training Courses.
5. The Commission fee is only valid for customers introduced by “Representative Name” to QMSrs
Non-Competence
During lifetime of this Agreement (as defined below) and for 12 months after the conclusion of this
Agreement, “Representative Name” shall not engage in any activity in direct competition with QMSrs,
including any competitive employment, business, or other activity, and shall not assist any other person or
organisation that competes, or intends to compete with QMSrs.
Termination of Agreement
1. Termination by Agreement or on Notice
Each party may terminate this Agreement at any time by mutual consent. This Agreement may be
terminated by either party at any time prior to the end of the agreement by giving sixty (60) days written
notice of termination. Such notice may be given at any time for any reason, with or without cause.
In addition, the Parties shall provide to each other a final report on the status of their work for the project
even though the work is not completed.

2. Termination on Default
In the event of a default the Parties shall have no further obligation to contribute to the cost of the project
and may require that the defaulting party transfer clear title and an unrestricted right to use the Intellectual
Property Rights in foreground and background information to the other party.
Mediation and Arbitration
In the event of any dispute between the Parties arising out of the construction, meaning or effect of any clause
or matter contained in this Agreement or of the rights and liabilities of the Parties, the Parties shall endeavour to
settle the matter through bona fide negotiations.
Failing an amicable settlement to any such dispute, each party may request, by sending a written notice to the
other party, that the dispute shall be referred to binding arbitration. This arbitration shall be subject to the
following rules:
 The Parties shall jointly appoint a single arbitrator. If the Parties cannot agree on the choice of an
Arbitrator, each Party shall appoint an arbitrator, and both arbitrators shall jointly appoint a third
arbitrator.
 Each Party shall pay its own costs and shall bear an equal share of all other arbitration costs as well as
the fees of the arbitrator.
 The Parties may jointly determine, by written agreement, the procedure to be followed by the
arbitrator in conducting the proceedings, or may request the arbitrator to do so.
 The hearing shall take place in the United Kingdom.
 The arbitrator shall issue a written award within thirty days following the completion of the hearing.
This award cannot include punitive damages or an award for costs.
 Subject to the provisions of the Commercial Arbitration Code, the award shall be final and binding on
the Parties.
Events Constituting Default
The following events constitute default:
 a Party becomes bankrupt or insolvent or goes into receivership
 an order is made or resolution passed winding down or dissolving a Party
 a Party ceases to carry on business
 a Party submits false or misleading information to the other Party or makes a false representation or
 a Party fails to proceed diligently with the Project
Non-Solicitation.
During the life of this Agreement and for a period of one (1) year thereafter, “Representative Name” will
not directly or indirectly recruit, solicit or hire any employee of QMSrs, or induce or attempt to induce any
employee of QMSrs to terminate his/her employment with, or otherwise cease his/her relationship with
QMSrs.
Confidential Information
At all times, both during the term of this Agreement and after its termination, both Parties will keep in
confidence and trust, and will not use or disclose, any Proprietary Information without the prior written
consent of an officer of the QMSrs, except as may be necessary in the ordinary course of performing the
services under this Agreement.
